## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of recent studies and the inherent complexity of measuring intelligence. The interaction between genetic and environmental factors is intricate, and current methodologies may not fully capture the nuances of this relationship. Additionally, intelligence is a multifaceted construct that may not be entirely encapsulated by IQ scores alone. Further research is needed to explore the dynamic interplay between genetics and environment in shaping intelligence across different populations and contexts.